{[showcards S:CT]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \S5, East plays the \ST and South wins the \SK. To the second trick South plays the \CT and you must discard something. 

Play the \SJ.

You know that East has no high \S honor or he would have played it to the first trick. So South has the \S A Q left, plus all those \C tricks. You need to have West switch to a \H if possible.

East must be expecting to lead a \S back when he wins the \CQ which you hope he holds. Your \SJ discard may make him rethink. If your \Ss were any good why would you be discarding a winner when all you had to do was toss a small red card?

Hopefully East will come to the conclusion that this is Suit Preference for a \H return and will play his \HJ. Hopefully.}
[Play "W"]S5

